.TH PALETTE-THEMING 1 "2026-03-11" "sway dotfiles" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
palette-theming \- live color palette theming system for sway
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Palette Theming system provides coordinated color palette switching
across sway window borders, the foot terminal, waybar, and the rofi
application launcher. It does
.B NOT
manage GTK, Qt, or Kvantum visual theming; those are handled separately
by
.IR 90-enable-theme.conf .
.PP
The system consists of four scripts and twelve palette theme definitions
under
.IR ~/.config/sway/themes/ .
Each theme carries two files: a sway
.I theme.conf
(color variables and
.B client.*
window decoration rules) and a
.I foot-theme.ini
(16-color terminal palette for the foot terminal emulator).
.PP
On every theme switch, the orchestrator
.B theme-selector.sh
(1) symlinks the chosen
.I theme.conf
as the active sway theme, (2) copies the
.I foot-theme.ini
to the runtime location read by foot, (3) pushes the new palette to all
running terminal instances via OSC escape sequences (no restart needed),
(4) reloads sway so window decorations update, and (5) regenerates the
waybar CSS, signals waybar, and (6) regenerates the rofi color variables.
.PP
A secondary script
.BR theme-toggle.sh
provides automatic light/dark switching based on local sunrise and sunset
times obtained from
.BR geoip.sh .
.SH KEYBINDINGS
.TP
.B $mod+t
Open the theme picker (wofi dmenu). Calls
.IR theme-selector.sh\ menu .
.TP
.B Waybar custom/theme (left-click)
Manually toggle light \[<>] dark palette. Calls
.IR theme-toggle.sh\ toggle .
.TP
.B Waybar custom/theme (right-click)
Enable or disable automatic solar-time switching. Calls
.IR theme-toggle.sh\ auto-toggle .
.SH FILES
.SS Core scripts
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/theme-selector.sh
Main orchestrator. Implements
.B menu
(wofi picker + apply) and
.B status
(waybar JSON icon) modes.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/theme-apply-foot.sh
Parses a foot-theme.ini and writes OSC 10/11/4;N escape sequences to
all writable
.I /dev/pts/*
PTY slave devices, applying colors to running terminals in real time.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/theme-waybar.sh
Reads the active
.I theme.conf
symlink, resolves
.BR $background-color ,
.BR $text-color ,
and
.B $accent-color
(one level of variable indirection supported), and generates
.IR ~/.config/waybar/theme.css .
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/theme-toggle.sh
Light/dark palette toggle based on solar time. Uses geoip.sh for
sunrise/sunset. Stashes the inactive variant as
.I theme.dark.conf_
/
.I theme.light.conf_
and swaps on request or automatically.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/scripts/theme-rofi.sh
Reads the active
.I theme.conf
symlink, resolves
.BR $background-color ,
.BR $text-color ,
.BR $accent-color ,
and
.B $selection-color
(one level of variable indirection supported), and generates
.IR ~/.config/rofi/Manjaro.rasi .
Called by
.I theme-selector.sh
on every theme switch and by
.I $update_rofi_theme
on every sway reload.
.SS Theme picker
.TP
.I ~/.config/wofi/config
Configures the wofi dmenu instance that renders the theme selection list
on
.BR $mod+t .
Sets geometry (35\[tmu]45%, centered), dmenu mode, case-insensitive
filtering, and icon display.
.TP
.I ~/.config/wofi/style.css
GTK CSS stylesheet for the theme picker window rendered by
.BR wofi (1).
Styles the border, background, entry list, and selection highlight.
.SS Theme data (one pair per theme)
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/themes/<name>/theme.conf
Color variable definitions (
.B $color0
\[en]
.BR $color15 ,
.BR $background-color ,
.BR $text-color ,
.BR $accent-color )
and sway
.B client.*
window decoration rules.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/themes/<name>/foot-theme.ini
Terminal palette in foot config format. Includes
.I ~/.config/sway/templates/foot.ini
for shared non-color settings.
.PP
Available themes:
catppuccin-frappe, catppuccin-latte, catppuccin-macchiato, catppuccin-mocha,
dracula, gruvbox-dark, matcha-blue, matcha-green, matcha-leaf, matcha-red,
nordic-bluish-accent, tokyo-night.
.SS Active theme (runtime \(em do not edit or track in git)
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/definitions.d/theme.conf
Symlink pointing to the selected theme's
.IR theme.conf .
Recreated by
.I theme-selector.sh
on each switch.
.TP
.I ~/.config/foot/foot-theme.ini
File copy (not a symlink) of the selected theme's
.IR foot-theme.ini .
Must be a copy so that foot can
.B include=
it without runtime-vs-source ambiguity.
Updated by
.I theme-selector.sh
on each switch.
.TP
.I ~/.config/waybar/theme.css
Auto-generated CSS with
.B @define-color
rules. Overwritten by
.I theme-waybar.sh
on each switch.
.TP
.I ~/.config/rofi/Manjaro.rasi
Auto-generated rofi color variables. Defines
.BR background-color ,
.BR text-color ,
.BR accent-color ,
and
.B selected-bg
for rofi. Imported by
.I ~/.config/rofi/config.rasi
via
.BR "@import \(dqManjaro\(dq" .
Overwritten by
.I theme-rofi.sh
on each switch.
.SS Templates
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/templates/foot.ini
Shared foot settings (font, scrollback, key bindings, cursor, bell).
Included by every
.I foot-theme.ini
via
.BR include= .
.SS Configuration references (files that use but do not belong to this system)
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/config
Includes
.I ~/.config/sway/definitions.d/theme.conf
to inject color variables into the sway config tree.
.TP
.I ~/.config/sway/modes/default
Binds
.B $mod+t
to
.IR theme-selector.sh\ menu .
.TP
.I ~/.config/foot/foot.ini
Includes
.I foot-theme.ini
and sets
.B initial-color-theme=dark
so new windows open with
.BR [colors-dark] .
.TP
.I ~/.config/waybar/style.css
Imports
.I theme.css
via
.BR "@import \(dqtheme.css\(dq;" .
.TP
.I ~/.config/waybar/config.jsonc
Defines the
.B custom/theme
module which calls
.I theme-toggle.sh
for status, click, and right-click actions.
.SH PROGRAMS
.BR wofi (1),
.BR swaymsg (1),
.BR pkill (1),
.BR awk (1),
.BR grep (1),
.BR foot (1),
.BR jq (1),
.BR mv (1)
.SH FLOW
.SS Theme switch (super+t)
.nr step 1 1
.IP \n[step]. 3
User presses
.B $mod+t
\[->]
.I theme-selector.sh menu
launches a wofi dmenu listing all directories under
.I ~/.config/sway/themes/
.IP \n+[step].
User selects a theme \[->]
.I apply_theme()
is called
.IP \n+[step].
.I theme.conf
for the chosen theme is symlinked to
.I ~/.config/sway/definitions.d/theme.conf
.IP \n+[step].
.I foot-theme.ini
is copied (not symlinked) to
.I ~/.config/foot/foot-theme.ini
.IP \n+[step].
.I theme-apply-foot.sh
writes OSC payloads to all
.I /dev/pts/*
\[->] running foot instances change colors instantly
.IP \n+[step].
.BR "swaymsg reload"
\[->] sway re-reads theme.conf \[->] window borders and title bars update
.IP \n+[step].
.I theme-waybar.sh
generates
.I ~/.config/waybar/theme.css
.IP \n+[step].
.I theme-rofi.sh
generates
.I ~/.config/rofi/Manjaro.rasi
.IP \n+[step].
.B "pkill -SIGUSR2 waybar"
reloads waybar CSS \[->]
.B "pkill -RTMIN+17 waybar"
refreshes the theme icon
.SS New terminal window (any time)
Foot reads
.I ~/.config/foot/foot.ini
\[->] includes
.I foot-theme.ini
\[->] loads
.B [colors-dark]
\[->] opens with the palette that was active when the last theme switch happened.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGUSR2
Sent to
.BR waybar (1)
to trigger a CSS stylesheet reload.
.TP
.B SIGRTMIN+17
Sent to
.BR waybar (1)
to refresh the
.B custom/theme
module output (icon and tooltip).
.SH WAYBAR INTEGRATION
The
.B custom/theme
module in
.I ~/.config/waybar/config.jsonc
shows a moon/sun icon and the active theme name. It calls
.IR theme-toggle.sh\ status
periodically, and on left/right click calls
.I toggle
and
.I auto-toggle
respectively.
.PP
All waybar module colors derive from the CSS variables defined in
.I ~/.config/waybar/theme.css
(imported by
.IR style.css ).
The three primary variables are:
.BR @theme_base_color ,
.BR @theme_text_color ,
and
.BR @theme_selected_bg_color .
.SH NOTES
.IP \[bu] 2
Live terminal recoloring works because writing to a
.I /dev/pts/N
slave device sends data to the terminal master's read buffer.
Foot (the master) processes OSC sequences as program output and updates
its palette without a restart.
.IP \[bu]
Foot does not support a
.B SIGHUP
config reload (the developer explicitly rejected it), so the OSC
mechanism is the only way to recolor running instances.
.IP \[bu]
GTK, Qt, and Kvantum theme application is
.B separate
and is performed by
.I 90-enable-theme.conf
(via
.IR enable-gtk-theme.sh )
on every sway reload. That system reads
.BR $gtk-theme ,
.BR $icon-theme ,
.BR $cursor-theme ,
and
.B $kvantum-theme
variables from
.I theme.conf
but its operation is independent of the palette system documented here.
.IP \[bu]
The matcha-* themes and dracula share the same Base16 Seti UI base
palette. Their distinction comes from the accent color and, for dracula,
the Dracula purple (#bd93f9) in the ANSI blue slot (regular4/bright4).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR foot (1),
.BR sway (5),
.BR wofi (1)
